{{Quote|The Tagges are a threat to the galaxy—They supply the Empire with ''ships'' and ''weapons, strip planets'' of their resources, and ''exploit'' their workers until their bodies give out. There are ''generations'' of blood on their hands.|[[Margo]]|<ref name="WOTBH Boushh">[[War of the Bounty Hunters – Boushh 1|''War of the Bounty Hunters – Boushh'' 1]]</ref>}}
The '''House of Tagge''',<ref name="WOTBH Boushh" /> also known as the '''Tagge dynasty''',<ref name="Aphra 2">[[Doctor Aphra (2020) 2|''Doctor Aphra'' (2020) 2]]</ref> or the '''Tagge Family''',<ref name="September Solicits">{{SW|url=news/marvels-september-2021-star-wars-comics-exclusive|text=The Fight for Han Solo Heats Up in Marvel's September 2021 ''Star Wars'' Comics &ndash; Exclusive}}</ref> was a [[noble]] and wealthy [[human]] family.<ref name="SWCT" /> They owned the [[Tagge Corporation]] company, which had [[mining]] facilities on [[Lucazec]]<ref name="Tarkin" /> and at least one subsidiary, [[Galacti-Stok]].<ref name="Survival">''[[Rey's Survival Guide]]''</ref> According to [[Chelli Lona Aphra|Chelli Aphra]], the Tagges even owned entire [[planet]]s.<ref name="Aphra 1">[[Doctor Aphra (2020) 1|''Doctor Aphra'' (2020) 1]]</ref> The House of Tagge ruled a region of [[the galaxy]] known as [[Tagge Space]].<ref name="Aphra 5" />

One of the family's notable scions was [[Cassio Tagge]],<ref name="Tarkin" /> from [[Tepasi]],<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> an [[Imperial officer|officer]] of the [[Galactic Empire]] who was elevated to the rank of [[Grand General]] and placed in charge of the entire [[Imperial Military]] after the [[Battle of Yavin]].<ref name="Darth Vader 1">[[Darth Vader (2015) 1|''Darth Vader'' (2015) 1]]</ref> According to [[Alliance to Restore the Republic|Rebel]] [[Commander-in-Chief]] [[Mon Mothma]], anyone who traveled among the [[Coruscant]] elite was well acquainted with the Tagge family.<ref name="Rebel Files">''[[Star Wars: The Rebel Files]]''</ref> The family shared their name with [[Finmos Tagge]] who served as [[Father of Chemicals]] in [[Coronet City]] on [[Corellia]] during the [[High Republic Era]],<ref name="Midnight Horizon">''[[The High Republic: Midnight Horizon]]''</ref> and [[Aurelia Tagge]] who owned the [[Nau'ur-class yacht|''Nau'ur''-class yacht]] ''[[Scarlet Dominion]]''.<ref name="Starships and Speeders">''[[Starships and Speeders]]''</ref>

==Members==
{{Quote|This family is a ''nest of vipers''. Dozens of relatives and stakeholders, every one of them a ''threat''. Any sign of weakness is an ''invitation'' to bury a knife in your back.|Domina Tagge|<ref name="WOTBH Boushh" />}}
Members of the House of Tagge included [[Killian Tagge|Killian]] and [[Sanya Tagge]], who led the Tagge Corporation. The two had four [[Youngling|children]]: [[Domina Tagge|Domina]], [[Orman Tagge|Orman]], [[Silas Tagge|Silas]], and [[Ulric Tagge|Ulric]]. Domina was the youngest of the children.<ref name="Aphra 35" />

[[Supreme Commander (Galactic Empire)|Supreme Commander]] of the [[Imperial Military]] [[Grand General]] [[Cassio Tagge]] was also a member.<ref name="Darth Vader 1" /> Cousins of Domina included [[Adelaide Tagge]] and<ref name="Boushh">[[War of the Bounty Hunters – Boushh 1|''War of the Bounty Hunters – Boushh'' 1]]</ref> [[Lapin Tagge]].<ref name="Aphra 28">[[Doctor Aphra (2020) 28|''Doctor Aphra'' (2020) 28]]</ref> The [[Imperial officer]] [[Brace Tagge-Faulken]], [[Layla Tagge-Faulken]] and her son [[Forthe]],<ref name="Boushh" /> and Domina's nephew [[Ronen Tagge]], the son of Adelaide and [[Felix Tagge]], were also members.<ref name="Aphra 28" />

